			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well I would do the following if I could:
<br />

<br />
1) Change description
<br />
2) Refund Points
<br />
to start with.
<br />

<br />
I use pet-canni for the sole purpose of getting mana. It doesnt matter where but i use it everywhere whether it be soloing (after mob down, sometimes using multiple pets for big bad mobs like PoV spiders), exp groups (Ldon, etc.) and raids (though it doesnt help that much except after a Mass rods, VT, some bosses which have so many hps like Empe). On classic PoP elem boss mobs i rarely need and use, cause i can't use my whole mana bar without being killed, can't even use more than 30% on mobs like phoenix where the MT gets charmed after a bit and new MT steps up to the plate.
<br />
In theory I wouldn't need to in our guild Ldon groups, but doing a norm adv. in 30 to 45 mins versus 45-75 can be an advantage.
<br />

<br />
I belong to the folks who has the luck to own the GoDS, making the whole pet-canni process even more effective. Even though i use pet-canni almost always I wouldn't mind getting rid of the whole tactic if we get something that compensates for it. (aggro reduce, better pets, whatever, lots of good ideas that wouldn't break game from many folks here). The simple reason being pet-canni is WORK (2 pet-canni cycles from lom to fm per adv.). I'd prefer being able to sit back and just do my standard stuff (pet-canni = standard stuff the way the game stands now for me)
<br />

<br />
We definately would need upgrades, cause just nerfing the tactic without being able to deliver a % of damage that comes through pet-canni will put us down on the dps roster a lot (exp-groups wise at least). And thats what we're about, high level of sustained damage where we rank among the best (still).
<br />

<br />
Solution of pet recast of 15 secs, will do more than nerf pet-canni. It will also eliminate some pet-chaining tactics where a new pet dies within 20-25 secs (15secs recast + 5-10 for new pet), thus weakening us additionally. Try chaining-rooting pet-canni PoV spiders that can hit for 500 hps. That wouldn't be possible with increasing recast massively.
<br />

<br />
Upgrades i could envision as game is currently:
<br />
aggro reduce capability (mainly for elem boss mobs).
<br />
better pets (higher lvl, more max damage, immunity to ae sometimes, remove all push components in a skill like /pet hold) to name a few.
<br />

<br />
Personally I look at mages the following way (if i would be able to change them):
<br />
max of 0-30% of damage comes from nukes. = lower nukes (max maybe around 1k just that its balanced)
<br />
70%-100% of damage comes from pets (but they must be usable in every situation, we can get some form of immunity to AE's and AE rampages for pets, there is no pushing from pets except if /pet push on, more max damage, special abilities like bane (prob cod nightmare), more hitpoints (possible since no pet-canni and not much of pet-chaining), natural durability, sta, etc. for pets.).
<br />

<br />
Extreme example (using high-end sustained mage dps of 270 which is quite a bit higher than i can achieve and aggro not a prob which can occur) is then pets are doing like 189 dps(using 30% nuke example), while nuking accounts for 71 dps....
<br />

<br />
Thats what I was expecting when i became a mage in Kunark era, and i'm not complaining about whether we're overpowerd or not, but just what I still think Mages should be.
<br />

<br />
These are just my thoughts and probably i'm in the vast minority (or the only one *G*) following this thread of thought. I'm however happy with my mage and would still choose the same class as my main if given the chance again whether they nerf us or not for the simple reason I'm a mage at heart.
<br />

<br />
Greetings,
<br />
Ethelwind<br />_________________<br /><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=325175"> <span style="font-weight: bold">Ethelwind Alandrial</span></a>
<br />
<A href="http://62.112.157.154"><span style="font-weight: bold">Eternal Flames, Solusek Ro </span> </a>
<br />
